61:## Validation Checklist
62:
63:- The manifest `workspace_root` and worker `cwd` match the intended workspace.
64:- Parallel workers that should finish before review are in an earlier stage than the reviewer or validator.
65:- The manifest records `invocation_cwd`, `cwd_requested`, and `cwd_resolution_mode` so you can explain how the workspace root was chosen.
66:- Relative-path specs and any deployment-specific absolute-path specs both resolve to the same intended workspace when you test portability.
67:- Every worker has a `prompt.txt`.
68:- Every worker has a `last.txt` or an explicit override path.
69:- The run produces `orchestration-summary.md` unless `write_summary_file` was disabled.
70:- Requested versus actual model, sandbox, and reasoning fields make sense.
71:- Child session IDs are captured when stdout exposes them.
72:- No worker writes outside its declared scope.
73:- The manifest `stage_plan` matches the intended parallel grouping.
74:- If `debug_log_file` is enabled, the trace reaches `manifest_written`.
75:- If a recovery run creates a second delivery attempt, run a reviewer worker against the final successful artifact before accepting it.
76:
77:## Efficiency Checklist
78:
79:- Use `low` reasoning for routine writer and reviewer workers.
